    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a collector-grade 2004 Honda S2000 (AP2), a definitive example of naturally aspirated precision. This unit features the F22C1 power plant, utilizing VTEC variable valve timing to achieve a linear power band and an 8,200 RPM redline. The longitudinal FR layout is paired with a close-ratio six-speed manual gearbox and a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal torque distribution. The chassis retains its factory-spec rigidity via the X-bone frame architecture and original double-wishbone suspension at all four corners. This vehicle is in turn-key mechanical condition, boasting all matching VIN tags on body panels, original 17-inch staggered alloy wheels, and a pristine soft top. Recent preventative maintenance includes a comprehensive valve adjustment and a full fluid flush with high-grade synthetics. No modifications; just a pure, unadulterated driving experience.",
